# Privacy Policy for INTENT

**Last Updated:** February 7, 2026  
**Effective Date:** February 7, 2026

---

## Introduction

INTENT ("the App") is operated by Clarity Labs. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our app.

**Key Point:** INTENT is designed for privacy. We do not collect personal information, do not require account creation, and do not track you across other apps or websites.

---

## Information We Collect

### Conversation Data
- **What:** The messages you send to the philosopher and the responses you receive
- **Why:** To provide the philosophical dialogue service and maintain conversation continuity
- **Storage:** Stored securely in our database (Supabase)
- **Identification:** Associated with an anonymous session ID, not your personal identity

### Session Information
- **What:** A randomly generated session ID created when you first use the app
- **Why:** To maintain your conversation history across app sessions
- **Storage:** Stored locally on your device and in our database
- **Note:** This ID cannot be used to identify you personally

### Usage Data
- **What:** Which concepts you've explored and conversation patterns
- **Why:** To track your philosophical journey within the app
- **Storage:** Associated with your anonymous session ID

---

## What We Do NOT Collect

We do **NOT** collect:
- ❌ Your name
- ❌ Email address
- ❌ Phone number
- ❌ Location data
- ❌ Device identifiers beyond the session ID
- ❌ Contacts
- ❌ Photos or camera access
- ❌ Microphone access
- ❌ Any personal information

---

## How We Use Your Information

1. **Provide the Service:** Process your messages through our AI system to generate philosophical responses
2. **Maintain Continuity:** Remember your conversation history and which concepts you've explored
3. **Improve the App:** Analyze usage patterns (anonymously) to improve the philosophical dialogue quality

---

## Third-Party Services

### OpenAI
- **Purpose:** Your messages are sent to OpenAI's GPT-4 API to generate philosophical responses
- **Data Shared:** Your conversation messages and context
- **Privacy:** Subject to OpenAI's privacy policy: https://openai.com/privacy
- **Note:** OpenAI does not use data sent via API to train their models

### Supabase
- **Purpose:** Database and backend infrastructure
- **Data Stored:** Your anonymous session ID, conversation messages, and concept tracking
- **Privacy:** Subject to Supabase's privacy policy: https://supabase.com/privacy
- **Security:** Data encrypted in transit and at rest

---

## Data Retention

- **Conversations:** Stored indefinitely unless you request deletion
- **Session Data:** Stored indefinitely to maintain continuity across app uses
- **Deletion:** You may request complete deletion of your data at any time (see "Your Rights" below)

---

## Data Security

We implement appropriate security measures:
- All data transmitted using HTTPS encryption
- Database access restricted and secured
- No data sharing with third parties except as described above (OpenAI, Supabase)
- Session IDs are randomly generated and cannot identify you personally

---

## Your Rights

You have the right to:

### Access Your Data
Contact us to request a copy of your conversation data

### Delete Your Data
Request complete deletion of all data associated with your session:
- **How:** Email intent.app.contact@proton.me with subject "Data Deletion Request"
- **Timeline:** We will delete your data within 30 days
- **Note:** Deletion is permanent and cannot be undone

### Opt-Out
You can stop using the app at any time. Simply delete the app from your device.

---

## Children's Privacy

INTENT is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If you believe a child under 13 has used the app, please contact us immediately.

---

## Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted within the app and on this page. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

---

## Important Disclaimers

### Not Medical or Therapeutic Services
INTENT provides philosophical dialogue based on Adlerian psychology principles. It is **not**:
- Medical advice
- Mental health treatment
- Therapy or counseling
- A substitute for professional help

**If you are in crisis or experiencing severe mental health issues, please contact:**
- Emergency services (911 in US)
- National Suicide Prevention Lifeline: 988
- Crisis Text Line: Text HOME to 741741

### Academic/Educational Purpose
The philosophical approach in INTENT is based on the book "The Courage to Be Disliked" by Ichiro Kishimi and Fumitake Koga, which presents Adlerian psychology concepts through dialogue.

---

## Contact Us

For questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your data:

**Email:** intent.app.contact@proton.me  
**Company:** Clarity Labs  
**Response Time:** We aim to respond within 7 business days

---

## Consent

By using INTENT, you consent to this Privacy Policy and agree to its terms.

---

## Technical Details (For Transparency)

**Data Flow:**
1. You send a message in the app
2. Message is sent to our secure database (Supabase)
3. Message is processed by OpenAI's API to generate a response
4. Response is stored in our database and displayed in the app
5. Concept tracking is updated based on the conversation

**Data Storage Locations:**
- Database: Supabase (cloud-hosted)
- AI Processing: OpenAI (cloud-hosted)
- Local Device: Session ID only

**Open Source:**
While INTENT itself is not open source, we are committed to transparency. Technical questions about our data handling are welcome.

